Important: I have used a command soon after the $ symbol to clearly show the command, but when using at the prompt you does not need the space.

-> How to add a new user to the system:

    $ sudo useradd User10

-> How to add a new user with a specific comment:

    $ sudo useradd -c "User 10" User10

-> How to add a new user with a specific Shell:

    $ sudo useradd -s /usr/bin/bash User10

-> How to add a new user without a shell:

    $ sudo useradd -s /usr/bin/nologin User10

-> How to change/ setup the password to a user:

    $ sudo passwd User10  //This command will prompt you to enter the password and confirm it.

-> How to lock a user account:

    Method 1: $ sudo useradd -l User10
    Method 2: $ sudo usermod -L User10

-> How to unlock a user account:

    Method 1: $ sudo useradd -u User10
    Method 2: $ sudo usermod -U User10
